	<TextInfo>
		<Text Type="Business Summary" lastModified="2015-10-12T06:31:15">Foreign &amp; Colonial Investment Trust PLC is a United Kingdom-based diversified investment trust. The Trust's investment objective is to secure long-term growth in capital and income through a policy of investing in a diversified portfolio of public listed equities, as well as unlisted securities and private equity, with the use of gearing. It also invests in markets like China and Latin America, and in companies that aren't listed on the stock market. In a single investment, the Trust invests up to 10% of the value of the total portfolio at the time of acquisition. It invests up to 10% of the total assets in other listed closed-ended investment companies, with an exception for companies that have themselves published investment policies to invest no more than 15% of their total assets in other closed-ended investment companies, in which case the limit is 15%. The Trust's investment manager and its Alternative Investment Fund Manager is F&amp;C Investment Business Limited.</Text>
		<Text Type="Financial Summary" lastModified="2015-12-02T23:38:34">BRIEF: For the six months ended 30 June 2015, Foreign &amp; Colonial  Investment Trust PLC revenues increased from L39.4M to L116.7M. Net income increased from L23M to L104.9M. Revenues reflect Gains on Investments and derivatives increase from L2.3M to L71.1M, Currency Exchange increase from L1.4M to L9.7M, Sundry income increase from L3K to L234K. Dividend per share increased from L0.04 to L0.05.</Text>
